Exercise 2¶

Create a list of formulas for modeling income with:

  • *height
  • height weight
  • *linear combination of all variables
In [12]:
# exercise 2
ggplot(heights, aes(x=weight, y=height)) + geom_point() + geom_smooth(method=lm)

Exercise 3¶

From the data, remove rows containing NAs. Fit the linear model with the formulas from exercise 2.

In [21]:
# exercise 3
#new_heights <- heights[complete.cases(heights), ]        
#new_heights <- na.omit(heights) 
new_heights <- heights %>% drop_na()
ggplot(new_heights, aes(x=weight, y=height)) + geom_point() + geom_smooth(method=lm)

Exercise 4¶

For each fit, calculate RMSE.

In [37]:
# exercise 4
mod <- lm(log(height) ~ log(weight), data = heights)

height.mod <- heights %>% add_predictions(mod) %>% mutate(pred=exp(pred), resid=height-pred)

ggplot(height.mod) + geom_point(aes(x=weight, y=pred))

Warning message:
Removed 95 rows containing missing values (geom_point).
In [36]:
mod <- lm(log(weight) ~ log(height), data = heights)

weight.mod <- heights %>% add_predictions(mod) %>% mutate(pred=exp(pred), resid=weight-pred)

ggplot(weight.mod) + geom_point(aes(x=height, y=pred))
